  "body": "### Component\n\nChisel\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nNone\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nRight now it is impossible to use forge-std remapping in chisel.\r\n```\r\nWelcome to Chisel! Type `!help` to show available commands.\r\nâžœ import \"forge-std/Test.sol\";\r\nCompiler errors:\r\nError (6275): Source \"forge-std/Test.sol\" not found: File not found. Searched the following locations: \"\".\r\n --> ReplContract.sol:6:1:\r\n  |\r\n6 | import \"forge-std/Test.sol\";\r\n  | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\r\n\r\n```\r\nThe same error occurs when trying to import project contracts which are using forge-std (tests, for example).\r\n\r\nThe error reason is following function:\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/c78a811a8af95fb1e029427583a07b2ca3a3fa51/chisel/src/session_source.rs#L312-L333\r\n\r\nOn line 331 it explicitly excludes forge-std remapping from list of remappings getting passed into solc",
